# elizaos/elizaos.github.io Daily Update (Jan 19, 2026)
## OVERVIEW 
The day's activity focused entirely on dependency updates, with nine new pull requests opened to bump various packages including `next`, `dotenv`, `better-sqlite3`, and `tailwindcss`, ensuring the project remains current with the latest library versions.

## KEY TECHNICAL DEVELOPMENTS

## NEWLY OPENED PULL REQUESTS
Nine new pull requests were opened, all focused on updating project dependencies. These include bumps for core frameworks and utilities such as `next` from 15.4.10 to 16.1.3 ([#223](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/223)), `dotenv` from 16.6.1 to 17.2.3 ([#224](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/224)), and `better-sqlite3` from 11.10.0 to 12.6.2 ([#222](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/222)). Development dependencies like `eslint-config-next` ([#221](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/221)) and `tailwindcss` ([#216](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/216)) were also updated, alongside other packages such as `@commander-js/extra-typings` ([#220](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/220)), `@faker-js/faker` ([#219](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/219)), `ora` ([#218](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/218)), and `date-fns` ([#217](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/217)). All these PRs are currently open and awaiting review.
